# 1. What is the Master List Framework?

The Master List Framework is a Google Apps Script framework that automates the processing, validation, synchronization, formatting, and reporting of monthly healthcare roster data.

The framework uses:

• Dashboard-driven configuration
• Template-first formatting
• Modular workflow architecture
• Batch processing
• Dashboard Quality validation
• Framework governance

The current production script is the implementation source of truth.

---

# 2. Repository Structure

## Current_Production

Contains the current approved production script.

Use when:

• Deploying
• Reviewing production logic
• Comparing releases

Never edit archived versions.

---

## scripts/

Contains modular source files.

Use when:

• Development
• Refactoring
• Architecture review
• Function review

---

## spec/

Contains engineering documentation.

Examples:

Framework Specification

Architecture Specification

Function Inventory

Sheet Definitions

Column Definitions

Mapping Documents

Governance Documents

Use these during design and review.

---

## reports/

Contains generated reports.

Examples:

Architecture Review

Function Inventory

Dashboard Quality

Timing Reports

Validation Reports

Review Reports

These are generated artifacts.

Do not edit manually.

---

## Archive/

Historical releases.

Use only for historical reference.

Never use archived files as implementation authority.

